PK — chalo isko bhi same style me “feel aaya” mode me todte hain 🔥
Low Level Design (LLD) bahut log confuse kar dete hain, but actually ye simple hai.

🧠 1️⃣ LLD kya hai (1 line me)
LLD = classes + objects + unka interaction
📍 2️⃣ System me LLD kaha aata hai
HLD → LLD → Code
🔥 Samajh like this:
🏗️ HLD
Order Service → Product Service → Payment Service

👉 Big picture (architecture)

⚙️ LLD
OrderService class
ProductClient class
PaymentHandler class

👉 Inside ek service kya ho raha hai

💻 Code
class OrderService {
   void placeOrder() {}
}

👉 Actual implementation

🧠 Aha Moment
HLD = system ka map
LLD = building ka blueprint
Code = actual construction
🎯 3️⃣ Purpose of LLD
✅ 1. Clean code
Readable
Structured
✅ 2. Maintainable
Change karo → system na toote
✅ 3. Testable
Unit test easy ho
🧠 Aha
Bad LLD = messy code
Good LLD = easy life
🧱 4️⃣ LLD Categories (MOST IMPORTANT 🔥)
🟢 1. Creational
💡 Meaning
Object kaise banega?
🔥 Example
Singleton → ek hi object
Factory → decide kaunsa object banana
Builder → step by step object
🧠 Aha
Creation control = Creational
🟡 2. Structural
💡 Meaning
Objects ka arrangement kaise hoga?
🔥 Example
Car = Engine + Wheel + Steering
🧠 Aha
Structure = skeleton of system
🔵 3. Behavioral
💡 Meaning
Objects baat kaise karenge?
🔥 Example
Order → Payment → Notification
🧠 Aha
Behavior = system ka flow / interaction
🧠 Ultimate Aha
Creational → banega kaise
Structural → judega kaise
Behavioral → chalega kaise
🔗 5️⃣ IS-A vs HAS-A (VERY IMPORTANT 🔥)
🟢 IS-A (Inheritance)
💡 Meaning
Child is type of parent
Example
Car IS-A Vehicle
Dog IS-A Animal
Code thinking
class Vehicle {}
class Car extends Vehicle {}
🧠 Aha
IS-A = inheritance
🟡 HAS-A (Association)
💡 Meaning
Ek object dusre ko rakhta hai
Example
Car has Engine
Library has Books
🧠 Aha
HAS-A = relationship
⚡ 6️⃣ HAS-A ke 2 types
🟢 Aggregation (Weak)
💡 Meaning
Objects independent hain
Example
Library → Books

👉 Library delete → Books still exist

🧠 Aha
Loose relation
🔴 Composition (Strong)
💡 Meaning
Objects dependent hain
Example
House → Rooms

👉 House delete → Rooms bhi delete

🧠 Aha
Tight relation
🧠 Final Shortcut (Interview Hack 🔥)
Instead of remembering UML symbols
Just think:
IS-A → inheritance
HAS-A → relation
Diagram hack
Car → Engine (HAS-A)
Car → Vehicle (IS-A)
🧪 7️⃣ Real Interview Thinking
❌ Galti kya karte log
Seedha code likhne lagte
✅ Sahi approach
1. Classes identify karo
2. Relationship define karo
3. Then code likho
🧠 Aha
LLD bina soche code = mess
LLD soch ke code = clean system
💥 Final Mental Model
LLD = "andar kya ho raha hai"
🔥 One Line Summary
LLD = design of classes, relationships, and interactions inside a system